Valene.Govender Photo: supplied Meela Bangtu (social worker) with the baby that was found abandoned near Verulam Secondary School. Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories THE Verulam Child and Family Welfare Society is appealing to anyone, who may know the relatives or family of a baby that was found abandoned near Verulam Secondary School ground on 24 August, to come forward.Social worker Meela Bangtu said: As social workers we are trying to get children reunited with their family instead of sending them to foster care institutions. The child was found abandoned by a passerby returning from work and took the child to Verulam police station. He was taken to Osindisweni. The child is in temporary care waiting for the parents to come forward. Anyone with the information, must contact Bangtu on 032 533 1046. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.